sec.p:
Since SKAT requires genotype data, SKAT was carried out on the ALL (Xu et al. 2013) and the WTCCC T2D (WTCCC 2007) data sets, using the top four principal components from PCA on these data sets as covariates. We find that PEGASUS gene scores and SKAT gene scores are correlated (r=0.44 and r=0.49;
P-values <2×10−16 and <2×10−16 for ALL and T2D, respectively) for both data sets (Figure S15, A and B). We also find that PEGASUS gene scores and unweighted SKAT gene scores are correlated (r=0.96 and r=0.94;
P-values <2×10−16 and <2×10−16 for ALL and T2D, respectively) (Figure S15, C and D).
